com.honeywell.mobility.print

Class PrintProgressEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.EventObject
      • com.honeywell.mobility.print.PrintProgressEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class PrintProgressEvent
extends java.util.EventObject
    This class contains the print progress event data. The print progress event is fired by the LinePrinter class or the LabelPrinter class during printing to inform the application when the printing is started and when the printing is completed.
    Since:
    1.0
    See Also:
    PrintProgressListener, Serialized Form
